    "Richard B. Vinson": "Maimon. Beth Habbechira, c. 8. sect. 10. & Cele Hamikdash, c. 7. sect.",
    "Ruckman, Dr. Peter S_": "The necessity of \u201cliving together\u201d will force the Christian to abandon the Bible doctrines on separation, consecration, individualism, personal accountability, and responsibility.\n1. Both ARE baptized with His baptism in Acts 2, and this is [v_Rom_6_4] brought home forcibly in Romans 6:4, where we are told that the baptism is associated with Christ\u2019s DEATH. The cup, then, and the baptism stand for Christ\u2019s actual death on the cross; they speak of suffering and death, but suffering and death ONLY. The actual spiritual transaction which takes place at Calvary, where the wrath of God is poured out on Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ who is taking the sinner\u2019s place, is a cup of a different size and shape. (John `[char_John_Ref]` R. Rice never did get the two cups to sit upright on the table, but they are there; see comments [v_Mat_26_39] under Matt. 26:39.) Notice that the baptism here is obviously NOT water baptism. Christ had been baptized in water three years before this time and so have the men to whom He is talking. Since Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` never baptized [v_Jhn_4_2] ANYONE in water (John `[char_John_Ref]` 4:2), and since He baptized ONLY with the [v_Mat_3_11] Holy Spirit (Matt. 3:11), we now reach the doctrinal truth that there is more than \u201cone baptism\u201d (Eph. 4), and that WATER BAPTISM is not the true \u201cone baptism.\u201d Notice that the baptism of our text [v_Mat_20_22] (Matt. 20:22\u201323) is a DEATH BAPTISM OF SUFFERING. No water is remotely connected with it in any way. As a matter of fact, WATER is the ONE THING THAT IS WITHHELD FROM IT WHEN IT TAKES [v_Jhn_19_28] PLACE! (See John `[char_John_Ref]` 19:28.) Thus ends forever the Catholic hocus- pocus and the Campbellite mumbo-jumbo about water producing a new birth. The baptism of Matthew 20 is future. \u201cYe shall [v_Mat_20_22] drink...and be baptized\u201d (Matt. 20:22\u201323), and it is not water; it is [v_Mat_3_11] a baptism of suffering. (For the other six baptisms, see Matt. 3:11 [v_Heb_2_9] and notes.) The cup is \u201ctasted\u201d by Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` in Hebrews 2:9, but this cup is only the taste of death! It is not the Father\u2019s cup of poured- out wrath. \u201cBut to sit on my right hand....\u201d The Lord grants them the privilege of His First Coming as a suffering servant to die; however, He does NOT grant to them the privilege of the Second Coming to be on His right hand and on His left. The reason is obvious to a premillennialist, since he accepts the answer to the enigma given in the Book of Revelation (Rev. 11). Again, our amillennial and postmillennial brethren do not know whether they are right-side up, upside-down, backside-forward, or frontside-rearward. If James and John `[char_John_Ref]` do not get these two places of honor\u2014who does? Answer: blank, if you are a Catholic, Lutheran, Episcopalian, Presbyterian, Methodist, Campbellite, Mormon, Jehovah\u2019s Witness, Christian Scientist, Seventh-day Adventist, or Rosicrucian. Answer: MOSES [v_Mat_17_1] AND ELIJAH, if you are a Bible believer\u2014see Matthew 17:1\u20133; [v_Rev_11_3] Revelation 11:3\u201310; Exodus 33:21; 1 Kings 17:1; Malachi 4:4\u20136; [v_Zec_4_11] Zechariah 4:11\u2013\n1. God and Satan are used interchangeably in the carrying out [v_2Co_12_4] of a punishment or chastisement (2 Cor. 12:4\u20138; Job 1\u20132; 1 Chron. [v_2Sa_24_1] 21:1; 2 Sam. 24:1; 1 Sam. 16:14). God is the originator; Satan is the [v_Lam_3_38] immediate author (Lam. 3:38; Job 2:3\u20136; Jer. 18:11).\n1. They must walk uprightly and speak the truth inwardly.\n1. The passage is \u201cdescribing the FRUITS of the regenerated life.\u2019\u2019\nverse 1 with Zechariah 14:\n1. So that is can be tried (Jer. 17:10).\n1. If the enemy\u2019s horse is faster, you lose.\n1. They must walk uprightly and speak the truth inwardly.\n1. The passage is \u201cdescribing the FRUITS of the regenerated life.\u2019\u2019\nverse 1 with Zechariah 14:",
